claim.claim-text:
23. A method of identifying a potential therapeutic agent for the treatment of a disease selected from the group consisting of: a muscle coordination disease, schizophrenia and depression, the method comprising: 
(a) contacting the potential therapeutic agent with &bgr;3GalT2 gene product; 
(b) determining whether the agent modulates &bgr;3GalT2 gene product, wherein modulation of &bgr;3GalT2 gene product identifies a potential therapeutic agent for the treatment of the disease.

25. A method of evaluating a potential therapeutic agent capable of affecting a condition associated with a mutation in a &bgr;3GalT2 gene, the method comprising: 
(a) contacting the potential therapeutic agent with &bgr;3GalT2 gene product; 
(b) evaluating the effects of the agent on the &bgr;3GalT2 gene product.

26. A method of determining whether an agent modulates &bgr;3GalT2 gene product, the method comprising: 
(a) providing a first preparation derived from the mouse of claim 2; 
(b) providing a second preparation derived from a wild-type mouse; 
(c) contacting a test agent with the first and second preparations; and 
(d) determining whether the agent modulates the first and second preparations, wherein modulation of the second preparation but not the first preparation indicates that the agent modulates &bgr;3GalT2 gene product.
